 Mthatha - SAPS District Commissioner, Major General David Kanuka, have sent a stern warning to those continuously taking the law into their hands after a 30-year-old man was brutally assaulted and killed after he alleged stabbed and killed a 21-year-old man and afterwards allegedly stabbed and injured another 24-year-old man at Tshangisa Street, Slovo Park, on New Year's Day at about 13h00. "It is alleged the 30-year-old deceased was at his home together with the 21-year-old deceased, who is his neighbour when they were seen coming from behind the house with the 21-year-old full of blood," said police spokesperson, Captain Dineo Koena. "The 21-year-old later collapsed and died." She said that when the 24-year-old victim tried to intervene, he was also stabbed by the 30-year-old on his upper body and was rushed to hospital in a critical condition. "When the community noticed the situation, they apprehended the 30-year-old and assaulted him," Capt Koena said. "He then succumbed to his injuries and died." Police are investigating a case of Assault GBH, and two cases of murder. "We urge people to have trust in the law. Let's not take law into our own hands. We will investigate and put behind bars those involved in the killing of our suspect," said General David Kanuka. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 